cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CR, cs.SOC

This paper deals with the analysis of political news and information being shared over Twitter, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of data mining techniques and natural language processing, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.SD (Software Engineering), respectively. The paper also discusses the impact of strategically disseminated polarizing information on public life, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks).
